day of the festival is known as kuningan. nyepi, or the hindu new year, also known as the day of absolute silence, is usually in march or april (next on march 31, 2014). if you are in bali in the days preceding nyepi, you will see amazing colorful giants (ogoh ogoh) being created by every banjar. on the eve of nyepi, the ogoh ogoh are paraded through the streets, an amazing sight which is not to be missed. there are good reasons to avoid nyepi as well, but for many visitors these will be outweighed by the privilege of experiencing 